  "doc_id": "19673",
  "text": "Previously, responses of isolated PVC and BSC neurons to DAsp were shown to decline with aging [CITATION_1] . We confirmed the decrease in D-Asp-evoked responses during aging in cultured PVC and BSC neurons and extended it to L-Gluevoked responses. We then saw evidence of the same decreases in excitability with aging in PVC and BSC neurons of intact ganglia whether we measured excitatory agonist-evoked or depolarizing current-evoked responses. The frequency of responders to excitatory agonist application decreased in old tail PVC and BSC sensory neurons in intact ganglia and isolated neuronal preparations compared to mature. Furthermore, the number of APs evoked by depolarizing current injection decreased while the threshold for firing an AP increased during aging in intact tail PVC and BSC neurons.",
